haser of groceries and\nbuilding materials; he buys for cash; I\ne must always maintain a large j\nbank balance for his chocking ac- I\ncount; l:e had $31,000 to the credit\ni hi- cheeking account the day be\ni> -r ilie bank closed. He was one\n.in few who knew that the crash\nwas imminent. He left his money in\nthe bank. He didn't even tell his\nfamily anc! Mrs. Woodley was caught\nher savings of years in the\nok. In appraising the character i\nr el \\V. J. Woodley, write this down.\nWhore the I'oor Lost\nSecond Ward Democratic I\nvY .'fare Club had $150.00 to its credit\nhi lh Savings Bank Trust Co.\n\"he C!;b had voted earlier in the\nuse c70 for the relief of the\nf lis; Ward. The poor will\nLaw to wait: the treasurer didn't\n(luck.': en the Club's bank ac-\nearly enough. Says Secre\nLni'is Boll: \"We weren't look\n1 a hie durn bank to bust right\nyiimi in our face.\"\nC'cnfidpnre\n*ii IV* man wearing an old felt\n-i an vvrccat that has seen\n.ai wear elbowed his way\nthe F.r.'jt ,'c Citizens National\nk Friday while the run was at\n?in. nuav.d his way into the.\nr-' fjuartars and said: \"I have I\nv 1 it dollars in Govern- I\n\"..elk bonds; if you need them for\ni' vet more money they are\ni: i.i.-j)!- 'mat man was,\nbright, owner cf Fowler j\nMiles Jennings, humble\noiled clothes and with!\ncis.ar stuck at a rakish\nIii mouth. rushed into the\nmcnring and said: \"I've\nl cC COO m Liberty Bonds;1\nmy f this bank needs 'em\n!:ry to my safe deposit;\n7!;!'.??? Hector Sick\nC niden County lives the\nC'.'v.t-U. imc cf the richest*\nfi.mi'i in there parts; they are'\nmoney; their money was\nSoy.nes Bank v.hen it bust\nlir. V. H. Cowell went to bed;\n1 madi iiim >iek. Ii made him\nonly because his own and\nmi: mom y was in the bank,\ni >r. CYwll is a proud man, he j\nc and confidence of\ni a iyhbeurs 'Jr. Cowell had in- j\na many of his friends and\nhi: :.i;v to put their money in i\nhe Savings Bank.\nt\nWcjaj for Violin j\n-V;,'.' syr;inio!V si re the fa*\nv.i 'N I'